    <!-- ==============================================
         FAQ
         ============================================== -->
    <section class="poke-faq-section" id="faq">
      <h1 class="poke-faq-heading">FAQ!!</h1>
      <p class="poke-faq-subheading">
        lil things people ask a lot about poke :3
      </p>

      <div class="poke-faq-list">
        <details class="poke-faq-item">
          <summary>is poke legal?</summary>
          <div class="poke-faq-a">
            yeah. poke is a privacy-focused layer for publicly available youtube data. in the united states, 17 u.s.c. § 512(a) covers intermediaries that transmit material without modifying it, and in the european union, directive 2001/29/ec covers temporary and incidental copies. poke does not rehost or redistribute copyrighted videos.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="poke-faq-item">
          <summary>who owns poke?</summary>
          <div class="poke-faq-a">
            poke was founded by ashley íris celeste and is built with love by ashley íris and amazing contributors :3
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="poke-faq-item">
          <summary>is poke private?</summary>
          <div class="poke-faq-a">
            yep!! poke is made to let u watch, search, and explore without ads or tracking following u around.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="poke-faq-item">
          <summary>does poke have every youtube video?</summary>
          <div class="poke-faq-a">
            yes — if it's publicly available on youtube, poke can show it :3
          </div>
        </details>
        
        <details class="poke-faq-item">
          <summary>how many people use poke?</summary>
          <div class="poke-faq-a">
            we don’t really know (privacy!) — but our best guess is here: <a href="/api/stats?view=human" style="color:#fff; text-decoration: underline;">/api/stats</a>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="poke-faq-item">
          <summary>why poke over youtube?</summary>
          <div class="poke-faq-a">
            poke is more lightweight, doesn’t shove ads at u, lets u download videos, and it’s really really really fast :3
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="poke-faq-item">
          <summary>how does poke protect my privacy?</summary>
          <div class="poke-faq-a">
            we proxy requests through our server so requests come from one shared ip (kinda like a private vpn layer), not yours.
          </div>
        </details>
        
        <details class="poke-faq-item">
          <summary>is fish legal in poke?</summary>
          <div class="poke-faq-a">
            fish.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

   
